title: 5.1 quake rattles alaska isle
author: Seattle Times Staffseattle Times News Services
text: PALMER, Alaska - A magnitude 5.1 earthquake jolted remote Adak in the Aleutian Island chain yesterday, a spokesman for the Alaska Tsunami Warning Center said.     The quake, reported at 12:47 a.m. (Seattle time), was centered in the Pacific Ocean about 70 miles southwest of Adak.  No damage or injuries were reported.
